ry. Thornton also provides a detailed analysis of wine consumer behavior and what studies reveal about the factors that dictate wine-buying decisions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aWine industry - United States. 0aWine industryzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  aalcoholic.  aamerican culture.  abeverages.  abusiness.  abuying decisions.  acapitalism.  aconsumers.  acooking.  aeconomic circumstances.  aeconomic concepts.  aeconomic principles.  aeconomics.  aengaging.  afood and wine.  agrape growing.  agrape markets.  agrape.  ahospitality.  alarge market.  aretailers.  aus wine industry.  awine distribution.  awine economics.  awine firms.  awine globalization.  awine markets.  awine production.  awine professionals.  awine tourism.  awine trade.  awine.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095701540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520957015423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520957015/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles